      <bioghist id="aspace_e682ee4b3f351fe682eac43a441da252">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Watson Fredericks Kinney was born on December 25, 1906, in Lock Haven, Pennsylvania, son of James Montrose Kinney and Helen Watson Fredericks Kinney. His father was president of the Kinney-Coons Company, Inc. of Yonkers, New York.</p>
         <p>Kinney attended Pelham High School and Phillips-Andover. He studied mechanical engineering at the Sheffield Scientific School, Yale University. His Yale relatives include two uncles, Gilmore Kinney, '07S and Orson A. Kinney, '18.</p>
         <p>After graduation from Yale in 1929, Kinney joined the Detroit Edison Company as an engineer in the production department. He was owner of the Watson F. Kinney Sales Engineering Company in Detroit, Michigan from 1958 until his retirement in 1974.</p>
         <p>(Extracted from: <title render="italic">
               <part>History of the Class of Nineteen Hundred Twenty-Nine, Sheffield Scientific School, Yale University</part>
            </title>, vol. 1, 1929.</p>
         <p>
            <title render="italic">
               <part>50 Year Record, Yale '29</part>
            </title>, 1979.)</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_b02693883bb8023166e502c96f46add4">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection consists of Kinney family correspondence, genealogical material, a memoir, a writing on the icaroscope, and a report on a Yale engineering inspection trip.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
